Freight Club API
Introduction

            Our vision is to offer you a better way to ship freight, the best way — easy, best priced, accessibility. That's how Freight Club was created, a 5-star B2B freight service now trusted by 100s of manufacturers, wholesalers, distributors and other businesses shipping freight in the US, Canada and US-Canada cross-border.
            We offer a front end user experience through www.freightclub.com as well as a full suite of APIs to help you build out integrations with your core systems.
        
Getting Started

            Prove out your integration concepts and test functionality on our provided sandbox API environment.  The token and the instructions are available in our documentation to get you started.

            


                    Download API Documentation
                


            Once you feel the integration is working as designed, go ahead and get started with a live account API token.
        
Available Postman Sample Collection

            The Freight Club set of APIs are available in a working example as a Postman Collection.  Download a .zip of the Collection and Environment here.

            The package is already pre-configured to work against the sandbox environment.

            Be sure to import the environment file and set it as the active environment before you run your first rating calls of the collection.


        
Connecting to Your Live Account

            If you don't yet have a Freight Club account, create one at www.freightclub.com

            Proceed to "Request Token" under the Manage API Tokens menu and your request will be reviewed by the Freight Club team. You will receive an email once the token has been approved and ready for use.
            All customers who use the Freight Club API must be on account for billing purposes.

            Once your token is ready, update your code to point to https://api.freightclub.com and replace the testing token by the one approved for your account.

            By default all quoted orders made under the API are not visible in the Freight Club application until they are booked.   Reach out to the support team if you would like to see quoted orders as well.
        
Support

            If you need any support or have any questions during the process please e-mail tech@freightclub.com. We will do our best to reply within 1 business day.
            If you do not receive a reply, please call us at 1 844 819 2187.

/Rate/GetRate




Returns all carrier rates for a single requested service levels open to your account.





Implementation Notes
This method will retrieve quotes for the specified Service Level, valid for both LTL and Parcel depending on Carriers that are open to your account.
This call performs faster than GetRates and is useful when performance is prioritized over selection.
The lowest price quote number is returned at the top level, however depending on availability, there may be many additional quotes to decide on.

The lowest price quote number is returned at the top level, however depending on availability, there may be many additional quotes to decide on.
GetRates mirrors how the Freight Club Quick Quote shows rates in the application.
